Body:
Is there a Kaa SDK for C# out-there? The kaaproject.com don't seem to support C#(.Net, but maybe there is someone alternative that allows me to build something in .Net that can behave like a device (kaa endpoint); Meaning sending messages (kaa data collections) and received messages (kaa configuration)?

Reading about the Kaa REST api, it don't seem to support sending/receiving messages. its more for administration.

Or maybe there is some other way that can be used to accomplish the same thing.

Currently, the Kaa platform supports the following programming languages:

  • C

  • C++

  • Objective-C
  • Java

Please see this link for more information.

"
